postcontent:
SALE ONLY. NO TRADES. PRICE IS FIRM

ITEM IS BRAND NEW AND UNFIRED WITH MANUAL AND MANUFACTURER STICKER.

DETAILS
Upper Receiver: A3 Flat-Top, Forged
Barrel Length: 7.5"
Barrel Contour: Medium
Barrel Material: 4150 Chrome Moly Vanadium Steel
Muzzle Thread Pattern: 1/2"-28
Chrome Lined: No
Barrel Finish: QPQ Melonite / Black Nitride
Twist Rate: 1 in 7"
Chamber: 5.56x45mm NATO
M4 Feed Ramps: Yes
Bolt Carrier: 1-Piece w/Integral Piston Strike Face
Muzzle Device: A2 Flash Hider
Gas System Length: Pistol, Short Stroke Piston Operated
Gas Block Diameter: 0.750"
Handguard: Samson 7" Extended Evolution Modular Rail, Free Float
Sights: None
Extras: One 4" Rail Section, QD Sling Swivel Adapter, Single Rail Piston Gas Block
Weight: 3.91 lbs (Without Rail Sections)

UPPER ASSEMBLY DESCRIPTION
This Adams Arms Tactical EVO PDW Gas Piston Upper Assembly is chambered in 5.56x45mm NATO and comes ready to fire right out of the box after installation onto any standard AR-15 pistol or registered SBR lower receiver. The Tactical EVO upper receiver line represents an outstanding value, and is the result of blending characteristics from the Adams Arms EVO Ultra Lite configuration with their Tactical Elite series to create a new, high performance platform at a more economical price. It features a melonite finished, 7.5" medium contour barrel with a 1 in 7" twist, making it capable of stabilizing medium- to heavy-weight projectiles of up to about 77 grains. Despite its short pistol length gas system, the piston chamber inside the PDW's gas block is the same size and has the same volume as Adams Arms' other gas system lengths. This means that unlike most AR-15 based systems that become notoriously unreliable once the barrel is reduced to less than 10" in length, the super short Adams Arms 7.5" PDW upper has the proper gas dwell time and bolt carrier velocity to allow it to function reliably and consistently in all conditions. It comes equipped with a free floating, 7" Samson Evolution Modular Rail Handguard that extends to surround the picatinny rail piston gas block on its bottom and both sides for a clean look and additional rail space if required. Additional features include M4 feed ramps, an A2 flash hider, bolt carrier group, charging handle assembly, one 4" modular rail section and one QD sling swivel socket adapter. 

BARREL DESCRIPTION
The upper's barrel has been finished inside and out with Adams Arms' proprietary QPQ Melonite treatment that bonds with the metal on a molecular level. Also referred to as salt bath nitriding, this treatment produces an extremely hard, slick surface on steel that resists carbon adhesion and increases corrosion resistance, extending a barrel's service life by reducing the friction produced inside the bore upon firing for a net decrease in bore surface wear over time. Nitriding converts the barrel steel's surface without any build-up, retaining all of the benefits of traditional chrome lining without suffering the accuracy degradation commonly encountered due to uneven application of chrome inside the barrel's bore. The end result is a barrel that's capable of producing accuracy on par with a match stainless steel tube, while also exhibiting the longevity and resilience of a chrome lined, mil-spec barrel. 

PISTON DESCRIPTION
All Adams Arms uppers feature a short stroke gas piston operating system, which prevents hot gas and debris from being directed back into the action upon firing. The result is a rifle that runs cooler, cleaner and more reliably than those utilizing a standard direct gas impingement system of operation. To ensure that damage doesn't occur to the buffer tube from carrier tilt, the bolt carrier is equipped with enlarged "skis" to help guide it into the receiver extension. The bolt carrier's solid steel, 1-piece construction incorporates an integral piston strike face to guarantee integrity over time, while the bolt assembly is spring loaded for proper lock-up and to help reduce bolt bounce and cam pin wear. All piston components are finished in QPQ Melonite for corrosion resistance and easy cleaning/maintenance. 

LIFETIME WARRANTY
All Adams systems come with a lifetime warranty provided you have not modified any of our parts or used them for anything other than their intended usage.

PAYMENT AND SHIPPING INFORMATION
Free Shipping.  No charge to ship insured with tracking to select US States.
Seller accepts payment in form of USPS money order only (or cash for local sales)

Thank you for viewing my ad!

AL-Mageddon

title: For Sale/Trade:  900 Rounds Federal HST .40S&W JHP
postcontent:
Priced lower than anywhere else online I can find.

For sale/trade is 900 rounds of Federal HST 155gr JHP for a .40S&W. I am asking far less than retail for cash offers.

It's easy to find the much less desirable Hydra-Shok ammunition on the shelf, and many people are intrigued by the "post" inside the hollow point. If you do the research, and I suggest you do, you will find that HST is extremely tough to beat.

That's why HST has almost never (in my experience) been for sale on the shelves at your local gun shop - I have only ever found it online, for a premium price, and in small or limited quantities. I have recently switched to a different caliber for my preferred CCW and cannot find anywhere that sells HST in bulk, must less a place with a single box in stock right now.
I live in Puyallup, but will be willing to drive a reasonable distance to meet - or even ship if you want to pay for shipping.

Take a look here for FBI Protocol test results on this ammunition
http://le.atk.com/ammunition/federal/handgun/details.aspx?id=567

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 3904
postcontent:
I have for sale a good condition Smith and Wesson 3904 9mm.  The 3904 is a a 3rd generation S&W semi-automatic pistol chambered in 9mm that is a very good mix of the very popular compact 3913 / 3914 and the the full size 5906 / 5904 series.  The 3904 offers the full size grip and 4" barrel of the 5900 series but the slim single stack design of the 3900 series.  These make great carry weapons with their slim design and light weight of an aluminum alloy frame.  3904's are some of the rarer 3rd generation smith's as they were only made from 1988 - 1990.  

This 3904 is in good condition with holster wear from carry.  It is traditional Da/Sa with slide mounted safety / decocker.  Gun is VERY reliable and is not ammo picky.  It does have adjustable rear sights and is extremely accurate.  Due to the longer grip and sight radius and can shoot this more accurately than my 3913 but it is substantially lighter than my 6904 or 5906.  Gun comes with 2 S&W magazines, 1 8 round and 1 9 round.  Also, if you have a 3913, 908, ext.., the 3904 mags can be used in those and they protrude out the end some.  I really like these guns just looking to free up some cash for another purchase.  Asking $350 but will consider reasonable offers.  Not really looking for trades but might be interested in S&W or Ruger revolvers in 32 H&R Mag or 327 Fed Mag, especially a single six in 32 H&R.  Located in Batesville but do occasionally travel to S and E side of Indy.
